HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 733
By Vital
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Eric Bruce "Pete" Arp.
WHEREAS, we were greatly saddened to learn of the passing of Eric Bruce "Pete" Arp
of Georgetown; and
WHEREAS, Pete Arp was a compassionate and faithful man who worked assiduously to
improve the quality of life for his family, his friends, and his community in numerous capacities;
and
WHEREAS, Mr. Arp was a dedicated tradesman of Plumbers and Steamfitters Local 43
for thirty-nine years; after his retirement, he opened Mountain Meadows Par-3 Golf and Driving
Range with his wife, brother, and sister-in-law, operating the establishment for twenty years;
and
WHEREAS, a gregarious man of varied interests, his favorite pastimes were meeting
and talking with new friends and going to the dirt track to watch his son, Skip, race; and
WHEREAS, deeply devoted to his family, Pete Arp always endeavored to remain true to
family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, he will be sadly mourned but fondly remembered by his wife of sixty-five
years, Jeanette Holland Arp; his son, Skip (Janice) Arp; his brother, Mickey (Rosemary) Arp; his
dear friends, Joe Bales and Tommy Basham; and a host of extended family members and
friends; and
WHEREAS, he was preceded in death by his son, Eric Bruce "Chip" Arp, Jr.; his
parents, Gordon and Melba "Bobo" Arp; and his grandmother, Mamie "Dee" Bruce; and
WHEREAS, Pete Arp leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in public
life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all his chosen
endeavors; and
HJR0733
010834
- 1 -

WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should remember the bountiful life of this exceptional
public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Eric Bruce "Pete" Arp, reflecting fondly upon his
impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the examined life with courage and
conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we extend our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family and friends of Mr. Arp.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
